During the course, students will receive an overview of the psychological and social factors of the work environment. Participants will get to know the possibilities of assessing and managing the positive and risk factors of the work environment and preventing work stress and burnout.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of the psychological and social factors of the work environment and of the possibilities of promoting occupational well-being at both the organizational and employee level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course a student: 1. Knows the psychological and social factors of the work environment and the general requirements of occupational health. 2. Explains the concepts and principles of promoting well-being at work and is able to apply them. 3. Applies the knowledge gained when drawing up a plan for the promotion of well-being at work.
